narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: pick a topic that really interests you. start thinking about it early. write down ideas that interest you throughout your years as a hshm major.stick with the deadlines b/c they just make things easier. dont be afraid to meet with the Rankin when picking an advisor hes super helpful

It's a mandatory class for the major, so you'll have to take it. The deadlines seem like they come up pretty quickly, but you'll appreciate them when it's winter break and you already have an outline and parts of your paper drafted.
Basically, it helps you write your thesis by making you hand in research reports, outlines, etc to your advisor by certain dates. I would only recommend this if you're an HSHM major.
